   "source": [
    "# Signal Filtering in Python"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import scipy.io.wavfile\n",
    "import scipy.signal\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# read ECG data from a wav file\n",
    "sampleRate, data = scipy.io.wavfile.read('ecg.wav')\n",
    "times = np.arange(len(data))/sampleRate\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(times, data)\n",
    "plt.title(\"ECG Signal with Noise\")\n",
    "plt.margins(0, .05)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Filter using an infinite impulse response (IIR) fitter\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create polynomials for a three-pole Butterworth low-pass filter\n",
    "b, a = scipy.signal.butter(3, 0.10)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filter the data using the default method\n",
    "filtered = scipy.signal.filtfilt(b, a, data)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(data, '.-', alpha=.5, label=\"data\")\n",
    "plt.plot(filtered, 'k', label=\"smoothed\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.axis([350, 500, None, None])\n",
    "plt.title(\"Low-Pass Butterworth Filter\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.plot(data, '.-', alpha=.5, label=\"data\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Effect of Different Cut-off Frequencies\n",
    "for cutoff in [.03, .05, .1]:\n",
    "    b, a = scipy.signal.butter(3, cutoff)\n",
    "    filtered = scipy.signal.filtfilt(b, a, data)\n",
    "    label = f\"{int(cutoff*100):d}%\"\n",
    "    plt.plot(filtered, label=label)\n",
    "    \n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.axis([350, 500, None, None])\n",
    "plt.title(\"Effect of Different Cutoff Values\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Isolate a small portion of data to inspect\n",
    "segment = data[350:400]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compare default (padded) vs Gustafsson’s method filters\n",
    "filtered = scipy.signal.filtfilt(b, a, segment)\n",
    "filteredGust = scipy.signal.filtfilt(b, a, segment, method=\"gust\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(segment, '.-', alpha=.5, label=\"data\")\n",
    "plt.plot(filtered, 'k--', label=\"padded\")\n",
    "plt.plot(filteredGust, 'k', label=\"Gustafsson\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.title(\"Padded Data vs. Gustafsson’s Method\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x288 with 2 Axes>"

     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Putting it All Together\n",
    "sampleRate, data = scipy.io.wavfile.read('ecg.wav')\n",
    "times = np.arange(len(data))/sampleRate\n",
    "\n",
    "b, a = scipy.signal.butter(3, 0.10)\n",
    "filteredGust = scipy.signal.filtfilt(b, a, data, method=\"gust\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))\n",
    "plt.subplot(121)\n",
    "plt.plot(times, data)\n",
    "plt.title(\"ECG Signal with Noise\")\n",
    "plt.margins(0, .05)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(122)\n",
    "plt.plot(times, filteredGust)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Filtered ECG Signal\")\n",
    "plt.margins(0, .05)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {

   "source": [
    "# Putting it All Together\n",
    "sampleRate, data = scipy.io.wavfile.read('ecg.wav')\n",
    "times = np.arange(len(data))/sampleRate\n",
    "\n",
    "b, a = scipy.signal.butter(3, 0.05, 'lowpass')\n",
    "filteredLowPass = scipy.signal.filtfilt(b, a, data)\n",
    "\n",
    "b, a = scipy.signal.butter(3, 0.05, 'highpass')\n",
    "filteredHighPass = scipy.signal.filtfilt(b, a, data)\n",
    "\n",
    "b, a = scipy.signal.butter(3, [.01, .05], 'band')\n",
    "filteredBandPass = scipy.signal.lfilter(b, a, data)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 3))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(131)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Low-Pass\")\n",
    "plt.plot(times, filteredLowPass)\n",
    "plt.margins(0, .05)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(132)\n",
    "plt.title(\"High-Pass\")\n",
    "plt.plot(times, filteredHighPass)\n",
    "plt.margins(0, .05)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(133)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Band-Pass\")\n",
    "plt.plot(times, filteredBandPass)\n",
    "plt.margins(0, .05)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
